In `lifecycle_for_scope`, it detects open models (started but not completed) and open runs (any run without RunCompleted). Then in `append_terminal_events`, it closes them. But there's a subtle issue:

When a model call completes but without a matching ModelCallStarted (i.e., unmatched completed), `append_terminal_events` won't detect it because it only looks for OPEN models (started but not completed). So it can't close something that was never started.

Similarly, unmatched completed runs (RunCompleted without RunStarted) won't be in `open_runs` because `open_runs = active_runs - run_completed`, and unmatched runs are in `run_completed` but not in `active_runs` (which requires started events). So they're correctly NOT in `open_runs`.

