So the lifecycle gap that `append_terminal_state_events.py` can't close is: it can close open models/runs (started but not completed), but it cannot fix unmatched completions (completed but not started). The unmatched completions need to be fixed at the source: ensure every RunCompleted has a matching RunStarted, and every ModelCallCompleted has a matching ModelCallStarted.

